article.headline: Oral Roberts 69, Chicago St 58
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green had 25 points and 10 rebounds to lead Oral Roberts past Chicago State 69-58 in a Mid-Continent Conference matchup Saturday night. Larry Owens added 11 points, five rebounds and five assists for the Golden Eagles (14-9, 9-2 Mid-Continent), who have won four in a row. David Holston led the Cougars (4-16, 3-6) with 17 points and Kevin Jones Jr. scored 15. Green made his first 16 free throws and finished 17-of-19 from the line. He had 14 points in the first half to help stake ORU to a 34-20 lead at intermission. Owens opened the second half with two free throws to give ORU its biggest lead, 36-20. Chicago State countered with a 13-4 run that cut its deficit to 40-33 with 12 minutes left. During the next four minutes, Holston sank two 3-pointers and two free throws to bring the Cougars within 53-48 but they could not get any closer. The Golden Eagles outrebounded Chicago State 41-34. A layup by Royce Parran gave the Cougars their last lead at 5-4 with 16:34 left in the first half. After the Cougars tied the game at 18 on a Camron Clay layup with 5:45 remaining in the half, Jonathan Bluitt hit a 3-pointer to ignite a 10-0 run for ORU.
